<h1>Listing transcriptions</h1>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>User name</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th>Picture</th>
      <th>Transcription</th>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
<!--     Awesome, now we have access to the additional features from CarriewWave to provide a thumbnail. We can use this in the transcriptions.index view to show a thumbnail next to the user_name.

Open the app/views/transcriptions/index.html.erb. We can then update the view table to use the thumbnail. Weâ€™ll use the same picture_url method, but pass the :thumb symbol to retrieve the thumbnail version. -->
    
    <% @transcriptions.each do |transcription| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= transcription.user_name %></td>
    <td><%= transcription.description %></td>
    <td><%= image_tag transcription.picture_url(:thumb) if transcription.picture.present? %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Show', transcription %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_transcription_path(transcription) %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', transcription, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
